<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1810" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1810">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/103.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 8, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Yesterday the Minister for Foreign Affairs, and later the Grand Vizier,
                            told the Ambassadors of the five Powers that the Sultan had decided to
                            remain in Constantinople but disclaims all responsibilty for the safety
                            of its inhabitants if the Bulgarians capture it. These communications
                            were reported by the Ambassadors to their Governments in identic terms,
                            without recommendations.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>